			<div class="ten columns center">
				<h2 class="text-color">Storyline and Merchandising</h2>
				<h4 class="bigtext uppercase letterspace bold">Product Development Consultant<h4>
				<p class="big thin">A joint project between Applied Minds and Amazon, Maker Shack Agency is about three kids - Wolfie, Merle, and Jo, who use creative thinking, hacking and maker skills, and problem solving to make the average day of middle school just a little bit more awesome. </p>
			</div>
		</div>


		<!-- 3 Columns -->
		<div class="row">


			<!-- Column 1 -->
			<div class="four columns">
				<p><i class="fa fa-comments-o icon huge"></i></p>
				<h4>The Challenge</h4>
				<p>Assist in the creation of storyline and merchandising plan for an Amazon Original Pilot.</p>
			</div>


			<!-- Column 2 -->
			<div class="four columns">
				<p><i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o icon huge"></i></p>
				<h4>The Process</h4>
				<p>Brought in by Executive Producer Jono Rosen, I was tasked with attending and contributing to writing staff meetings, as well as exploring options for and assisting in the prototyping process for items that would become props in the show as well as part of a merchandising plan. While the show was originally about just Wolfy and Merle - both boys - after some lengthy discussion with the writers, female character Jo was introduced (I later found out that the writers had designed her after what they thought that I must have been like as a kid - their assumptions were largely accurate.) As the show was beginning to take form, I explored several options for kits comprised of electronics components that could be purchased at a low price point, would be simple enough for kids to be able to build at home with some light documentation, and fun enough to be featured as props on the show. Eventually, we landed on the "Smell-O-Meter," featured as part of the pilot episode.</p>
			</div>


			<!-- Column 3 -->
			<div class="four columns">
				<p><i class="fa fa-bolt icon huge"></i></p>
				<h4>The Result</h4>
				<p>Maker Shack Agency was released as an Amazon Original Pilot, receiving an average Amazon user rating of 4.3/5 stars, and an IMDB rating of 8.2/10.</p>
			</div>


		</div>
